METHOD
01. Inocalate 2 ml of rich medium (LB, YT, or Terrific Broth) containing the appropriate antibiotic with a single colony of transformed bacteria. Incubate the culture overnight at 37°C with vigorous shaking.
02. Pour 1.5 ml of the culture into a microfuge tube. Centrifuge at maximum speed for 30 seconds at 4°C in a microfuge. Store the unused portion of the original culture at 4°C.
03. Remove the medium by aspiration, leaving the bacterial pellet as dry as possible.
04. Resuspend the bacterial pellet in 100 µl of ice-cold Alkaline lysis solution I by vigorous vortexing.
05. Add 200 µl of freshly prepared Alkaline lysis solution II to each bacterial suspension. Close the tube tightly, and mix the contents by inverting the tube rapidly five times. Do not vortex! Store the tube on ice.
06. Add 150 µl of ice-cold Alkaline lysis solution III. Close the tube and disperse Alkaline lysis solution III through the viscous bacterial lysate by inverting the tube several times. Store the tube on ice for 3-5
minutes.
07. Centrifuge the bacterial lysate at maximum speed for 5 minutes at 04°C in a microfuge. Transfer the supernatant to a fresh tube.
08. (Optional) Add an equal volume of phenol: chloroform. Mix the organic and aqueous phases by vortexing and then centrifuge the emulsion at maximum speed for 2 minutes at 4°C in a microfuge. Transfer the aqueous upper layer to a fresh tube.
09. Precipitate nucleic acids from the supernatant by adding 2 volumes of ethanol at room temperature. Mix the solution by vortexing and then allow the mixture to stand for 2 minutes at room temperature.
10. Collect the precipitated nucleic acids by centrifugation at maximum speed for 5 minutes at 4°C in a microfuge.
11. Remove the supernatant by gentle aspiration as described in Step 3 above. Stand the tube in an inverted position on a paper towel to allow all of the fluid to drain away. Use a Kimwipe or disposable
pipette tip to remove any drops of fluid adhering to the walls of the tube.
12. Add 1 ml of 70% ethanol to the pellet and invert the closed tube several times. Recover the DNA by centrifugation at maximum speed for 2 minutes at 4°C in a microfuge.
13. Remove all of the supernatants by gentle aspiration as described in Step 3.Take care with this step, as the pellet sometimes does not adhere tightly to the tube.
14. Remove any beads of ethanol that form on the sides of the tube. Store the open tube at room temperature until the ethanol has evaporated and no fluid is visible in the tube (5-10 minutes).
15. Dissolve the nucleic acids in 50 µl of TE (pH 8.0) containing 20 µg/ml DNase-free RNase A (pancreatic RNase). Vortex the solution gently for a few seconds. Store the DNA solution at -20°C.
TRANSLATE
01.将挑取的单克隆放入加入相应抗生素的培养基中，37°C震荡过夜培养。
02.取适量菌液置于1.5ml离心管中，4°C最大转速离心30s，未被使用的菌液暂时4°C保存。
03.抽吸去除培养基，尽可能干燥细菌沉淀。
04.加入100 µl冰冷的碱性裂解液I并将菌体悬浮。
05.加入200 µl新制备的碱性裂解液II于细菌悬液中。 紧闭管盖并快速翻转5次以使菌体充分裂解，结束后将试管放在冰上
06.加入150 µl预冷的的碱性裂解液III， 紧闭管盖并快速翻转，将试管在冰上存放3-5分钟。
07.4°C最大转速离心5min，将上清转移至新的离心管中。
08.(可选操作)添加等体积的苯酚：氯仿。 将有机相和水相涡旋混合，4°C以最大速度离心2分钟，将含水上层转移至新管中。
09.在室温下添加2倍体积的乙醇，从上清液中沉淀核酸。涡旋混合溶液，然后将混合物在室温下静置2分钟。
10.4°C下以最大速度离心5分钟收集沉淀的核酸。
11.重复以上3步操作，轻轻抽吸除去上清液。将试管倒置在纸巾上，以使所有液体排出。
12.加入1 ml 70％的乙醇至沉淀中，密闭管并倒置几次。4°C以最大速度离心2分钟回收DNA。
13.重复以上3步操作，轻轻抽吸去除所有上清液。
14.将离心管开盖并室温放置5-10min以将残留的乙醇全部蒸发。
15.将核酸溶解在50 µl 含有20 µg / ml但不含DNase的RNase A的TE（pH 8.0）中。轻轻涡旋溶液数秒钟，将DNA溶液储存在-20℃。
Vocabulary
Rich medium:丰富培养基
Single colony：单克隆
Microfuge tube：微型离心管
Centrifuge：离心机
Resuspend the bacterial pellet：重悬细菌沉淀
Ice-cold Alkaline lysis：冷的碱性裂解液
Equal volume：等体积的
Aqueous upper layer：水性上层
Precipitate：沉淀
Ethanol：乙醇
Supernatant ：上清液

